-- Whole-model verification summary
----------------------------------------------------------------------

-- Summary 1: Model captures registration of incoming flights with permissions, actors, resources, interfaces, and state transitions.
-- Summary 2: Safety assertions check authorization, resource access, well-formedness, and post-state semantics.
-- Summary 3: Liveness predicates demonstrate reachability of acceptance criteria and test scenarios.
-- Assumption 1: Flight number uniqueness is modeled via distinct resource targets with different grants.
-- Assumption 2: Empty/null input is modeled by requiring encrypted and authenticated channels.
-- Assumption 3: Post-states are abstract and not linked to concrete flight data.
-- Open issue 1: Edge case assertions (ec_safe_1, ec_safe_2) are heuristic and may not fully capture the intended behavior.
-- Open issue 2: The model does not include explicit flight data (e.g., flight number, type, time) as signatures.
-- Open issue 3: Some assertions (e.g., sr_assert_authentication) may be too strong for all operations.


